def: A genus of hexactinelline sponges, having a long stem composedof very long, slender, transparent, siliceous fibres twisted togetherlike the strands of a color. The stem of the Japanese species (H.Sieboldii), called glass-rope, has long been in use as an ornament.See Glass-rope.
A carriage hung on poles, and borne by and between two horses.Milton.
To be distasteful; to taste ill or disagreeable. [Obs.]Dangerous conceits are, in their natures, poisons, Which at the arescarce found to distaste. Shak.
The office of a preacher. "The preachership of the Rolls."Macaulay.
To compress; to shut up. [Obs.] Burton.
To be employed in manufacturing something.
To drink immoderately; to carouse; to booze. See Booze.
